                                                    The workflow of the project:                                      
1)Single IDP chain built as a straight rod, replicated into many chains, compressed
into a cube to form an artificially dense configuration while running NVT simulation  was prepared in a separate upstream script. This script picks
up from that saved box and runs the coexistence simulation.

2)Each amino-acid sequence is first coarse-grained: every ten residues are merged into one bead, and each
bead is given a mass, size, charge, and hydrophobicity (lambda) averaged from its residues following the
HPS-Urry model (The computation of rearranged CG model parameters is shown in report too).

The equilibration brings the system from its artificial starting arrangement to a more stable, lower-energy
state before measurements begin.Its time approximately lasts 1microsecond for FUS-LC protein which is enough for discarding artificial dense phase 

The production is the main run, where the chains move and assemble naturally according to the HPS-Urry model.
Over microseconds protein chains separate into a dense protein-rich slab and a surrounding dilute phase,
if they undergo liquid-liquid phase separation at those conditions.

While running, the script records the energy, forces, temperature, and radius of gyration of the chains.

The analysis extracts the phase concentrations from the slab, following Dignon 2018(Mammen Regy R, Zheng W, Mittal J. Using a sequence-specific coarse-grained model for studying protein
liquid-liquid phase separation. Methods Enzymol. 2021;646:1-17. doi: 10.1016/bs.mie.2020.07.009. Epub 2020Aug 17. PMID: 33453922; PMCID: PMC7873582) a paper which Regy at al 2021 is based on. 
For each frame it finds the largest cluster of chains (the condensate) from their centre-of-mass distances, shifts that slab to the
centre of the box, and counts how many beads fall along the z-axis to build a density profile. The dense
concentration is read from the middle of the slab and the dilute concentration from the edges, both converted
to mg/mL.  Averaging the second half
of the run gives the final coexistence concentrations, which are the main result.
